      • readWords

        public static java.lang.Object readWords(java.io.DataInput dataInput,
                                         int storageType,
                                         int totalWords,
                                         long offset,
                                         int totalBytes,
                                         CNUDataConversions cdc,
                                         java.lang.Object outArray,
                                         int outOffset,
                                         java.util.Vector<java.lang.String> ignoredFormatErrors)
                                  throws java.io.IOException
        Reads words from from a DataInput This is DICOM specific because strings are stored as bytes not 16 bit unicode characters and padded with nulls to even byte lengths.
        Parameters:
        dataInput - input to read words from
        storageType - the type of data to read
        totalBytes - total number of bytes to read (should be even bytes and multiple of word size)
        outArray - array to store read words in. If null creates new array
        outOffset - offset location into outArray to start storing read words at
        Returns:
        object an array (or string) of the storage type filled with read words
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - thrown on failure reading from dataInput
